--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages util_linux.

The util-linux package contains a large variety of low-level system utilities
that are necessary for a Linux system to function. Among others, Util-linux
contains the fdisk configuration tool and the login program.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: util_linux
       util_linux_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: util_linux
       util_linux_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  util_linux_state
    Specify predetermined 'util_linux_state' variable (string).
    Notice: 'util_linux' is a core package and can therefore not be removed.

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DEPENDENCIES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PACKAGES
  util-linux-ng: >= 2.17
    RedHat, CentOS

  util-linux: >= 2.22
    Gentoo

